{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S3 fa49: Thread ref + source mode through the code-reading gates)]\n\nAudited this child's contribution to the parent's acceptance/success criteria; every absence cross-checked against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 6d56 materialize core, S2 70c7 cache+janitor, S4 30b3 attested signing, S5 b7fa CLI/MCP surfacing, S6 1ba5 docs). This child is the gate-threading / re-rooting slice; the union of children covers every parent criterion. No uncovered parent criterion. EMPTY G3 findings list.\n\n4-bucket coverage map (parent AC -> covering child/children; this child's role called out):\n- Parent AC1 (no code-reading gate reads the server's working tree in attested mode; all read a faithful snapshot materialized at the pinned SHA) — FULLY covered, with THIS child as the PRIMARY OWNER of the re-rooting half: its AC1 (each of the five gates accepts ref+source; attested reads the snapshot dir, never the server's working tree), its AC3 (all three dispatch touchpoints — gate_ops, completion.py, operations._assemble_context — CONSUME the snapshot handle, not just the interface signature), its AC6 (a gate tolerates an absent/being-GC'd snapshot by re-materializing, never reading a partial tree), and its AC7 (regression test asserts the attested verdict is IDENTICAL regardless of the server's checked-out branch — the behavioral contract reproducing this session's wrong-branch false-negative). S1 owns the faithful-materialization half (its AC1/AC2). Heart of this child. Clean.\n- Parent AC2 (signed verdict records verified_at_sha + reproducible over identical content) — FULLY covered by S4 (30b3 record+sign+in-toto) atop S1's immutable-SHA basis. THIS child THREADS the ref + points the gate at the pinned snapshot that S4 signs over; its AC7 (identical verdict regardless of checked-out branch) directly reinforces reproducibility. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. the signing act itself (this child's Scope: \"Out: signing rules (S4)\"). Not an absence (S4 covers signing).\n- Parent AC3 (local source mode reads the in-place checkout AND cannot produce a signed verdict) — covered SPLIT: THIS child owns the \"reads in-place checkout\" half (its AC4: local mode reads the in-place checkout, dirty allowed, flagged unsigned, repo_root IS the read root; attested uses repo_root only to locate the object DB); S4 (30b3 AC3) owns the \"cannot sign\" bar. This child explicitly marks the run unsigned and notes \"S4 bars signing\" — clean reader/enforcer split, no uncovered half.\n- Parent AC4 (concurrent gates on same/different SHAs run without git-lock contention or cross-op corruption; no worktrees; atomic population; delete-on-last-close) — FULLY covered by S1 (atomic population, no-worktree, no index.lock/config.lock contention) + S2 (single-flight, delete-on-last-close). THIS child contributes the CONSUMER-side tolerance (its AC6: ENOENT -> miss -> re-materialize, never a partial tree) that makes eviction-under-an-open-handle harmless from the gate's perspective. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. the population/eviction mechanism. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC5 (snapshot cache + janitor reclaim disk under pressure without disrupting in-flight reads) — FULLY covered by S2 (sole owner). THIS child's AC6 (absent/being-GC'd snapshot tolerance) is the gate-side complement that lets reclamation proceed without disrupting a reader. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. the reclaim mechanism (this child's Scope: \"Out: snapshot/cache internals (S1/S2)\"). Not an absence.\n- Parent AC6 (private-repo fetch failure surfaces a descriptive, actionable credential error) — FULLY covered by S1 (raises; its AC5) + S6 (documents; its AC1/AC2). The fetch is S1's coalesced step; this child claims none. STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC7 (portable: no external tar; no hardcoded /tmp; flock+mkdir fallback) — FULLY covered by S1 (implementation; its AC4) + S6 (docs; its AC5). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child (this child's Scope: \"Out: snapshot/cache internals (S1/S2)\"). Not an absence.\n- Parent AC8 (all six child stories closed; make lint + full test suite green) — STRUCTURAL/meta epic-completion criterion; covered by the existence of all six children (this child is story #3 of 6 in the roster) + each child's own green-bar obligation. Not an absence at this child.\n\nParent out-of-scope behavioral collapse (covered, not an absence): the parent's \"code-review gets a single repo copy at a single ref ... like every other operation (no base+head pair)\" is owned at the BEHAVIOR level by THIS child (its AC5: code-review uses a single snapshot at a single ref, no base+head pair). The complementary back-compat/expand-contract default (existing callers passing neither param get ref=origin/main, source=attested) and consumer-tolerance are also this child's own ACs (AC2 documented/configurable defaults; AC6 stale tolerance). (The SURFACE-side retirement of the pre-existing base/head/--diff-file controls is a standing G4 seam between S3 and S5 — a consistency concern about WHO retires the surface controls, not a G3 union-coverage gap; the single-ref code-review obligation is CLAIMED by a child here.)\n\nSuccess-criteria narrative (\"every code-reading gate verifies a client-specified, immutable, reproducible snapshot of the project at a pinned SHA — NEVER the server's mutable checkout — safely under concurrent use ...; signed verdicts reproducible and bound to verified_at_sha; the unsigned local mode preserves the single-developer verify-before-push workflow\") decomposes onto AC1-AC3. The \"NEVER the server's mutable checkout\" clause is precisely this child's core deliverable: re-rooting the gate file tools / cfg.repo_path / pai_tools root onto the snapshot dir across all three dispatch touchpoints, with the AC7 regression test as the behavioral proof that the wrong-branch false-negative this epic exists to kill cannot recur. The \"client-specified\" surfacing is S5; the \"immutable/reproducible/pinned-SHA\" basis is S1; the \"signed/verified_at_sha\" act is S4; the \"unsigned local preserves verify-before-push\" reader half is this child (AC4), the signing-bar half is S4. No uncovered obligation introduced.\n\nNamed-consumer / delegation cross-checks (covered-by-named-consumer, not absences): this child's Scope explicitly delegates signing rules to S4 (30b3), CLI/MCP surface schemas to S5 (b7fa), snapshot/cache internals to S1/S2 (6d56/70c7), and the architecture ADR (authored in S2, cross-referenced here). Each delegated obligation is claimed by the named sibling. Covered-by-named-consumer.\n\nNote (scope, NOT a G3 finding): the standing G4 dependency-gap on sibling S4 (30b3) — routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py's dependency_hashes()/_rehash()/claim-gate freshness re-check across the S3<->S4 seam, where THIS child re-roots only \"the gate's file tools (pai_tools root / cfg.repo_path)\" and lists completion.py/pai_tools.py/mcp_server.py (NOT attest.py) in file_impact — is a CONSISTENCY (G4) concern about WHO threads the handle into the attestation hashing path, not a G3 union-coverage gap. The corresponding parent obligations (AC1 snapshot-only reads, AC2 reproducibility, and the ref-coherence clause) remain CLAIMED by children (this child's AC1/AC3/AC7 and S4's AC5), so the union covers them. G3 union-coverage of the parent criteria is complete.\n\nConclusion: this child cleanly covers the gate-threading / re-rooting slice (ref+source on all five gates; attested reads the snapshot dir across all three dispatch touchpoints; local in-place read flagged unsigned; back-compat origin/main+attested defaults that are configurable not hardcoded; consumer absent/GC'd-snapshot tolerance; single-ref code-review; the wrong-branch-invariance regression test) of the parent criteria — it is the PRIMARY OWNER of parent AC1's re-rooting half and the \"reads in-place checkout\" half of AC3. No parent acceptance/success criterion is left uncovered by the roster. No G3 finding for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782527138997832001,"uuid":"76383223-890f-4351-b506-50c6d312464e"}